      "solution": "s = input()\n\nenergy = 0\nwhile True:\n    for i in range(1, len(s)):\n        if s[i-1] != s[i] and s[i-1].lower() == s[i].lower():\n            s = s[:i-1] + s[i+1:]\n            energy += 1\n            break\n    else:\n        break\n\nprint(s)\nprint(energy)\n",
      "statement": "In the spirit of particles and anti-particles, let's define characters and anti-characters as lowercase and uppercase characters respectively. As we all know particles meeting anti-particles annihilates each other and produce energy. In a string, an anti-character annihilates a character if they are <<adjacent>> and are the <<same letter in opposite cases>> (e.g., {{a}} and {{A}}), releasing 1 unit of energy in the process.\n\n    baACCcB → b(aA)C(Cc)B → bCB + 2 energy units\n\nGiven a string of characters, annihilate characters until a stable string is reached and record the energy released. A stable string is a string where no annihilation can occur.",
